BABAJIDE Olumide Olowoyeye aka J12, who doubles as a singer and a legal practitioner has released his highly anticipated single, ‘Ileri.’ J12, who has been experimenting with sounds since he was eight in church, released ‘Ileri,’ his third single under Fame Records on June 24.   AVRS, NCC meet stakeholders in Lagos     All eyes are on Nigeria, we must do better, says Sleek     The Ibeji Live Experience returns to Terra Kulture on July…   After releasing his debut single in 2019, J12 has successfully combined practicing law with entertainment. J12 also expressed that the new single chronicles the current situation of the country saying the “soul” twist of the single is an inspirational rendition that will lift the spirits of Nigerians. J12 revealed that part of his plans in the nearest future is to have a couple of collaborations with Tuface Idibia, Wizkid, Drake, and Usher while his hobbies that informed his inspiration to write good music include cooking and traveling.